abstract: VERMONTVILLE, Mich., Aug. 18.--A boiler explosion occurred yesterday near this village. E. Darrow and Leonard Garringer were instantly killed. The body of the latter was blown to fragments. The boiler was used to generate steam for a thrashing machine engine.

abstract: ASBURY PARK, N.J., Aug. 30.--The second carnival of the season was held on Westley Lake this evening. The lake, which is a mile in length, was covered with boats decorated with Chinese lanterns and fancy colored fire.  The shore was lined with people to witness the  procession on the water. The houses along the lake were handsomely decorated with Chinese lanterns, and there was a big display of fireworks.
